*Want to win free developer related swag?* contribute to open source projects like *<#CBBAW6Z3R|community-browser-extension> or <#CCQSQ2C6L|crankshaft>*  and earn yourself a cool shirt.
<https://hacktoberfest.digitalocean.com/>

Hacktoberfest is being run by DigitalOcean GitHub and Twilio, I cannot cheat you into getting a free shirt but if you submit 5 Pull Requests total on CrankShaft and/or the dev extension you’re eligible.

I will label some items on the dev extension Hacktoberfest to indicate great issues to tackle as a new person to the repo. we also have a “good first issue” label which means the same thing.

HubSpot’s own JinJava template language(HubL without the HubSpot) is an open source project. So that too might be a good hacktoberfest project
<https://github.com/HubSpot/jinjava>

Hallo Diana, kennst du diese beiden Links schon? <https://inboundaddons.com/inbound-member/#features> und  How to create a HubSpot Membership Site | Inbound Addons
<https://inboundaddons.com/how-to-create-a-HubSpot-membership>...
